The paper discusses the creation and analysis of an Open Information Extraction (OIE) corpus, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR) that involves extracting relations and their arguments from text. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of the OIE corpus for downstream tasks such as knowledge base construction and open question answering, which are relevant to the sub-fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper compares the OIE corpus to existing knowledge bases such as DBpedia, which falls under the sub-field of databases (cs.DB).
